    "In this system, speakers focus more on conveying meaning than paying attention to sentence structure.",
    "Krashen emphasizes the importance of the acquired system compared to the learned system.",
    "On the other hand, the learned system is associated with formal instruction where students engage in formal study to understand the target language.",
    "This includes learning syntax rules and other formal aspects (Krüger, 2023).",
    "In a different style (Teflpedia, 2023) states that Stephen Krashen's acquisition-learning hypothesis is the most crucial aspect of his theory on second language acquisition."
